# ── /api/* routing notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ▸ Replit (dev & autoscale deployment):
#     The application router maps /api/* to the API server service (port 8080)
#     automatically — no redirect needed.
#
# ▸ Netlify:
#     netlify/functions/api.ts intercepts all /api/* requests and proxies them
#     to the AnimeSalt upstream (animesalt-api-lovat.vercel.app) with the same
#     path transforms the Express server applies.  No redirect needed here.
#
# ▸ Other static hosts (Cloudflare Pages, GitHub Pages, etc.):
#     These hosts cannot proxy to a dynamic API server.  Deploy the
#     artifacts/api-server as a standalone Node.js service and add a redirect
#     rule pointing /api/* to that service's URL.
#
# SPA fallback is handled by the host-specific config (netlify.toml for
# Netlify, or the host's equivalent).
